This paper is about information retrieval modelling, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper proposes a unified framework that combines generative and discriminative models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, it is likely to also fall under the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
